 reading for students and lecturers in star studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture actors and actresseszFrance. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aCatherine Deneuve.  aFrench political culture.  aRepulsion.  aTristana.  ablank heterosexualities.  afemale homosexual activity.  afilm scholarship.  alesbian relation.  aone-woman show.  astar persona.  astar studies.1 aAsibong, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirchall, Bridget, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDowning, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDowning, Lisa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEvans, Peter William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHandyside, Fiona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Sue, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Sue, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJohnston, Cristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarshall, Bill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmall, Pauline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeiner, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614143940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141439423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141439/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d20